w][col]\n                if next_col < 0 or next_col >= n or grid[row][col] != grid[row][next_col]:\n                    break\n                col = next_col\n            else:\n                result[ball] = col\n        \n        return result\n```\n\nThis solution simulates the path of each ball through the grid. It iterates over each ball, starting from the top of each column, and follows the direction indicated by the board in each cell. If a ball hits a wall, a \"V\" shape, or an invalid move, it gets stuck, and we record `-1` for that ball. If the ball successfully reaches the bottom, we record the column it exits from.", "estimated_date": 1609027200000}